 of interest to final year undergraduates, postgraduates, academics and those interested in the areas of Victorian literature, Victorian studies, postcolonial studies, history and popular culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aOrphans in literature. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aBermuda.  aCanada.  aCharles Dickens.  aGeorge Eliot.  aNew South Wales.  aRose Macaulay.  aThe Mystery of Edwin Drood.  aVictorian culture.  aWuthering Heights.  acriminal orphan.  aforeigner.  aorphan texts.  apolicing empire.  apost-colonial studies.1 aPeters, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613059440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130594/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles